data.title: Crown Prince Frederick, later Frederick VIII, of Denmark and Princess Louise of Sweden
data.meta_description: Louise's coiffure is showing signs of bustle era complexity, but she wears a crinoline dress with close or, possibly, banana sleeves dating this to the later 1860s.
data.text:
Frederick visited Sweden in 1868 to get to know Louise and this photo could date to that time. Sweden had not rallied to Denmark's aid during the Prussian-Danish war so relations between the two Scandinavian powers were tense. Her marriage was celebrated in Stockholm and gifts were Swedish to boost Sweden's sagging economy.

From Wikimedia.
